aratus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text after Cordano 1992\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>This document is one of a large deposit (c. 150) of lead tesserae found in a storeroom of Athena's sanctuary at the archaeological site of Kamarina. The occurrence of the same name on both faces a and b would suggest, according to the editor, a double use of the lamina by the same person. However, it is worth noting that the name is integrated on both faces.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Cordano 1992 142 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002437\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002437\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 52.0920 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> 54.0892 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">      \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[198,201,204,207,210,212,215,218,221],{"id":199,"html":200},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cspan class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"aba\">section a\u003C/span>  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class